oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photomontage showing the Lafayette Escadrille memorial near St. Cloud, France, two Manchurian scenes during the Sino-Soviet war, a newly-built high school in Lincoln County, Tennessee, a advertisement for a film entitled Our Modern Maidens, an advertisement for Plough's Soap, a picture of actress Lillian Gish, a map dated 499 A.D. unearthed in Palestine, and two images showing a bridge being built over the Cumberland River in Celina, Tennessee. 16 x 21.5 in. Forms part of the Nashville Newspaper Rotogravure Digital Images Collection.
